params.newAdmin: the address of the admin to add Only admin(s) can add new admin

buy().details: Buy a unique token      * One address can only hold one token as the token ID is based on a hashed version of the buyer's address      * The price of the token is based on a bonding curve function

returns._0: current minting limit Only admin(s) can add new admin

params.x: the x value in the bonding curve graph Assuming current bonding curve function of y = x^2 + basePrice

returns._0: price at the specific position in bonding curve

params.oldAdmin: the address of the admin to remove Self explanatory

sell(uint256).details: Sell a unique token      * Sell and burn the token that has been minted

params.tokenId: the ID of the token being sold - The price of the token is based on a bonding curve function - Will check if token is legitimate

params.limit: the current token minting limit Only admin(s) can change this variable

params._newContract: the address of the newly deployed SPACE token In case if token address ever changes, we can set this contract to point there

params.admin: the address of the admin to check Self explanatory

withdraw(address,uint256).notice: TODO: Make it multisig so not one admin can withdraw all
